  <scopecontent id="aspace_f1229b28ccad8d37f3dbeff0fac01015">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Album of photographs of well-known psychologists, prepared during the mid-1950s by Harry Jacobs, a psychology graduate student. Also, photographs of various laboratories in the Psychology Department in Morrill Hall, ca. 1910-1940; photograph taken at James Gibson's retirement party; photograph of Professor Papez; photograph of K.M. Dallenbach; photograph of Madison Bentley; and photograph of Thomas A. Ryan and Jeff Bitterman.</p>  </scopecontent>
